values:
My last entry was 19 weeks ago :O

My dad said that if I get into a good med school in Taiwan, I have to go back. Now I'm wishing my marks aren't high enough to get into the good schools, wishing I slacked off a bit more in grade 11. *wry laugh*

I'm really really really looking forward to going to University if Toronto. I have maps printed out with locations of stores, banks, bars :P, anything that seems useful written in. I have 5 different versions of my course timetable this year, in case I don't get into the courses I want, and all 4 years of my double major degree planned out. I'm really excited to be more independent; I even have recipes that I want to try out all bookmarked!

I want to have a say in where I go. Isn't it my choice? Yeah, sure, med school is like, totally hard to get in, but why cant you believe that I can get in in Canada? My Chinese is nowhere as good as the people's in Taiwan, for obvious reasons, so what makes you think I can compete with them? I get tired reading even just a paragraph of Chinese. Plus I can't even read all the words! I think it's because I'm their only hope of someone in our generation of becoming a doctor. Urgh. Talk about pressure.

My Saturdays are boring. I usually just kick back, relax, and don't get anything done.

Well, I did do two things. I started studying Solubility unit for Chemistry. If I'm effective (?), maybe I'll get this unit done today. Thats what I'm hoping. And then Acid/Base unit over 2 days. Redox on Wednesday, and cram session on Thursday, and then my provincial on friday.

I'll study math. Soon. I've done too many practice provincials to want to study much. At least I know what I'm doing.

I downloaded the form for applying to university in Taiwan. Tried to fill them out but without my moms help, I totally didnt know what to fill in each blank. Can't guess the meaning from 2 words. There's so many forms. I wrote my chinese name like....5 times. Literally. AHH

Basically, I wasted a whole bunch of time today. Maybe because the second I sat down to start studying, I felt sleepy. O__O 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

24!!!!: "They once named a street after Jack Bauer in California- Jack Bauer Avenue. However, they had to get rid of it because of too many reported deaths on the road- nobody crosses Jack Bauer and survives."

~~~~~~~~

Wow, the posting thing is different. I must've not been on Livejournal for WAAAY too long.

Btw, I opened an account on facebook, so you can find my entries so far under the "My notes" section.

I feel like crying. Stress does weird things to me. But I shouldn't cry. I won't cry. And I'm tired. And now I'm complaining.


I'm working on a scholarship essay right now, and it's really stressing me out. The submission deadline is Dec 1. Tomorrow I have to get the counselor to edit and give some input. I have to take it home, re-edit, and I'm hoping to get more input. This means that I will be submitting this essay either on the 29th or 30th. That's barely making the deadline a little bit too close for comfort.

Yeah, I was looking forward to school today. It would've made my life a lot easier to be able to see the counselor today.

Chem midterm tomorrow. I dont know how well that's going to go. I haven't studied quite enough, but I cant bring myself to focus for any longer.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Now for the happy stuff.

SNOW! SNOW! and lots of it too!!! I am such a immature kid when it comes to playing in snow. If only I have a toboggan...Yesterday's snow was perfect for snowball fights. Today's, however, was too soft and powdery and dry, which was fun when you threw it up and it floated down. Our half-assed attempt at building a snowman sure failed though. Our snowball "fight", if you could even call it that, was rather scary. Sandra gave up on the powdery cold stuff, and ended up chucking chunks of ice which sounded like glass shattering once they hit the pavement. Scary. Definitely.

School is all I ever talk about. My life is pathetic.

Friday was our math test. Today was our marks being handed back. Guess what. I got 37/40. Not perfect, but I'm actually happy. I'm working really hard on math right now, trying to improve my mark. I'm happy. Really.

Tom said that he was more nervous than I was. Apparently he's scared of crying girls. And of me crying. He was sooo relieved when I was happy with my mark.

On another note, accounting is now confusing. Maybe cause all I do is chat in class. I didnt even pick up a pen today.

And chem, well, Sam is my new seat buddy. I wonder how that's going to go. He talks too much. Umm, and I need a new lab partner too. No one tell him, but I would rather not work with sam. Haha. He's a great person and all, but not the one I would choose to do labs with.

from 1. How do you deal with stress? I bake desserts, eat them, along with other chocolates and talk to my friends. Sometimes when its really bad, I cry. 2. Do you have a favorite "comfort food" and what is it? Chocolate, for sure. And cookies. 3. Do you have a "comfort activity" and what is it? Baking. Writing in here. Ranting at my friends. 4. What days depress you and why? Test days. 5. What days excite you and why? Friday, for the obvious reason, weekend! Umm, I like Wednesdays too. Dance class. Hehe.

I HAVE AN "A" IN MATH! I HAVE AN "A" IN MATH! I HAVE AN "A" IN MATH! I HAVE AN "A" IN MATH! I HAVE AN "A" IN MATH! *dance* 

I am totally estatic.

..and I was also exuberant when I found out my mark of 7.5/10. Lol, I think somethings wrong with me.

I've got a test and two quizzes tomorrow. Wish me luck. Missed Grey's Anatomy to study!! AHHHHH *runs into wall*

Accounting Test: well, theres a couple steps which are crazy. I talk most of the class so, basically no idea whats going on. And my work is so sloppy. Theres white-out and scribbles everywhere. Basically it looks like chicken scratches.

Chem Quiz: theres some things I dont quite understand. I -should- go in for flex BUT Kevin's playing basketball tomo. Hard decision. Maybe halfway through I'll leave.

Math Quiz: uh-oh. At least its trig. And I have faith in myself this time. If the teacher gets my mark messed up one more time, I'm gunna go tell him. Its frustrating seeing a lower mark on my test (my actual mark) than the one posted on the window.

Uh oh....highs and VERy high!? I should a wear sign on my back. "DANGER: Is borderline, histronic, nar..." ...you get the idea. Wow. Just. Wow.

Eric Dane aka McSteamy is becoming a regular this season! Yayyy. What a hottie.



But too bad for Finn. He's only around for one or two more episodes.

I'm going to make it my goal to blog at least twice a week. I felt so..blank after writing, and thats a -good- thing. I hate thinking about things that I should be worried about. Only gets me more worked up and frantic, even when I shouldn't be.

<lj-cut text="School">

Two days till math test. I'm really nervous. I think Jonathon is wrecking my self-esteem. Lol. I know its bad to blame things on other people but he's had tutor so he knows how to do the questions and can do them really fast. Me, on the other hand, nope. Not a clue how to even start the question. That really bugs me. And the fact that because of this, I can't learn anything at school because there's aways an "answer key" right beside me.

In accounting, I got my test back, even though I handed it in last class, because the teacher made an error answering a problem I needed help with. It was pretty sweet~ I only discovered this error when Waina and I were discussing the test. Lol. And I changed an answer or two that I knew was not quite what the teacher was looking for. Anyways, who can pass up a chance to cheat? *nervous laugh* Pfft, plus its just accounting. Leona's brother and this other girl were like talking through the whole test and the teacher didn't hear them. It was kind of pathetic. Me and Sandra were waiting to ask questions and laughing at that. XD

Got our meningoccal shots today. To prevent infection of the meninges, the protective layer of fluid(?) in the brain, or something like that. It wasn't that painful. Especially amusing was how the guys would punch each other on the arm right after. Ouch. Well my arm started getting stiff, especially since I took the shot in my right arm (stupid, yeah, I know) and I some trouble writing in straight lines with nice writing. Oh well~ Tom was saying at break that he can't "raise it up", in Chinese of course, and Jason walked by and heard. He moved towards where another group of girls was and repeated what Tom said. And Kitty got -very- hyper. She still was on the way home. Yeah, we were arguing over how she learned the meaning of the word.

Hmm, I should take my camera around with me too. Too bad I'm too lazy to take pictures and I would rather spend lunchtime playing basketball or doing something meaningful.

Meaningful..hmm. Yeah, my whole life has become this frantic rush to accomplish something worth being proud of. It's a whole new burden on my shoulders that I just want to forget about. I'm still young, still have lots of time to achieve success, right? Right!?

</lj-cut>

~~~~~~

Wentworth Miller = hawt

I would watch 24 but ..no time. Wait, season 6 starts in January!? Sweet. Maybe I will have time by then. *fingers crossed*

I'm totally a TV junkie/couch potato, whatever you want to call it. :D

I just dont dont dont and I repeat, dont understand math! Argh. This is so frustrating. I dont know whether it's because Mr. Ahn teaches too fast and I'm not used to his pace or I'm getting stupid. Well, I'm used to not having to work very hard to understand things and still do well, but THIS I am struggling with. Whoever said gr 12 math is as hard is gr 11 lied. And I'm really really scared for AP Calculus now. And Physics. meep. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ I am stressed. Seriously stressed. To the point where I can't sleep at night. I think I've crammed my schedule to the max. Guess theres no basketball team for me this year. :( Gotta start sending my university applications. Ontario is accepting them already. Hoping for admission based on my last years grades because frankly, I dont have such high expectations for my marks this year. And gotta get a move on scholarships. Deadlines for so many have passed, and I totally DID NOT care about it. Whee~ *looks guilty*

I've barely had a moment to think ever since school started.

-->Been busy looking at scholarships. Like Jen said, competition is crazy. I've seen ones where all the winners have either started some sort of club at school or organized a group to bring attention to something. I have nothing I really excel at, as I've kinda dabbled in assorted 

-->I have a spare this semester!! Its been really helpful in allowing me to get my homework done at school. At home, I look up university or scholarship information and review if I feel up to it. Math started becoming a challenge already, and this is the easiest chapter! Transformations and Reflections. *sigh* Well, I didn't understand. Maybe I will in the morning, after mulling it over in my sleep. Spent and hour and a half on it. I'm getting there.

-->Dance class started! I'm in competitive jazz this year, and not quite up to the standards of the other girls yet, but I feel like I'm catching on real quick. We were doing jumps, splits in the air, and then landing on one foot. I almost went over on my ankle, the left one, the weak one. It wobbled for a bit, until I put my hand down on the floor. I dont want to be a cripple. :D

-->Basketballl~~~ I missed it over summer, but now its back. The grade 12's from last year are gone, so the ones left are not as good, meaning I have more of a chance to take shots and drive in to the net. Still gotta work on those layups BUT I -did- make a shot from the 3 point line. That totally made my day.

-->Can't forget about TV. I have a new favourite show, Prison Break. Mondays @ 8. Its gory and/or suspenseful at times so I go through some episodes with my eyes covered half the time.
House. Tuesdays @ 9. This is the best best best show I've seen in a long while. Especially the last episode. The season premiere didnt live up to the hype in the commercials.
Grey's Anatomy. Thursday @ 9. Am I ever excited for this! After reading the short summaries, I can't wait. And last season's ending, with Izzie quitting the internship program, and Merideth/Derek/Finn/Addison still in that love triangle..err, square? ..I'm excited.
Desperate Housewives. Sunday @ 9. AHH I miss Paul the plumber. At least I -think- that's his name. All I remember is his hotness. Lol. And the dentist from last season was creepy. And theres definitely trouble brewing in the Solis' house. I can't wait for this show either!

-->I'm tutoring kids english. Kinda new to this still. Don't really know what fun stuff that exaberates learning I can do. Any suggestions? And anyone remember what books they read for novel study in Gr 5? Or what they were learning at grade 3? Comments would be appreciated :D

Now, I am tired. And its only 9:30. What's up with that? Studying drains all my energy away.

Well, I finally got around to donation a pint (500ml) of my precious blood. Its almost 1% of my body mass :O *dies*

<lj-cut text="My experience">

When I went in, the lady looked soo confused. Apparently I look about 13. I got a lil sticker that said "First time donor on it". Whee~~ Then they poked my finger to see my iron/hemoglobin levels. It was soo cool watching my blood just float there. Yeah, it floated and finally sunk, unlike other peoples' which just sunk. I have low iron levels, almost didnt pass the 'test'. But the poking finger thing, that hurts. I could feel my pulse after tho, that was pretty awesome.

So I filled out the questionnaire, they took my temperature, blood pressure, heart rate. I'm at 66!! I'm assuming thats a good thing, and means I'm in shape.

Soo..I chatted with someone who was also waiting his turn. All the chairs were full. He said it was the first time he's ever seen that happen. I was so nervous, especially since I'm afraid of needles. All the nurses took it slow, and explained what they were doing. They filled tubes with my blood to send for testing in Calgary. Theres chemicals in the bags to keep the blood from coagulating, and is also why the machines swing back and forth. Since I didn't want to see the needle poking into my arm, they got a cloth and covered it :P

So since my blood comes out slow I got a lil thing to squeeze. Took about 15-20 minutes to fill the bag. Wow. After, when I was resting, all of a sudden I got really lightheaded. Almost fainted. My eyesight went blurry, breathing got laboured. Everyone rushed to my side, pressed cool clothes on my forehead, neck, and wrist. And I got orange juice. So when I felt better, and an hour after I arrived, I had a couple oreos, more glasses of juice and left.

My mom and I went to Staples, and then Wal-Mart. We were on our way to get my vision checked when I started feeling really lightheaded again. I sat down by the shoe aisle where they have seats. Then I lay down. After awhile, I threw up. Ew. They had to get the cleaning guy to come. A whole bunch of Wal-Mart employees were helping me to feel better. Gave me water and ice pack for free. Then I threw up again. Twice in a row. They had to get the cleaning guy to come AGAIN. I feel bad for that fellow. At least it was on linoleum and not carpet. Ugh... Eventually they called an ambulance to come look at me. It was an hour later that they came, since I dont constitute as an "emergency". Oh well. By that time I felt so much better, and after taking my BP and HB again, I got to go home. Where I threw up again. Only this time it was in a garbage can. 

So, last night I lay in bed for the longest time, finally got the energy and felt good enough to eat dinner at 10PM and then went to bed.

Today, I am mostly confined at home. There goes my Canada Day plans. At least I can walk upstairs now. Although it quickly brings my heart rate up to 120 beats/min. Thats crazy. And I lost 4 pounds. Wow. Shocking effects.

</lj-cut>


However, I am glad that I helped 3 people with my blood. I don't regret giving blood because I didnt know it would have this effect on me. Now I know. And I'll wait till I'm older to give again.

School. This is what my life revolves around these days. And studying. Only 3 more days till I'm free. I should sound more excited, but frankly, I'm too tired to be exhausted. I've been making charts on topics for socials, not I need to memorize them. I'm almost on the verge of 'winging' the essay questions. I dont know what it is. Maybe the weather. Definitely end of school. But I'm getting burnt out. There's no more steam for me to run on. After this I need a nice long break.








Too bad I'm taking summer school. *sigh*

I've been coming home and napping every day this week. I'm just so tired from studying every night and focusing every single miniscule fibre of my attention on retaining the information that I've studied.

Ophthalmologist. Specialist eye doctor.

~~~~~

I've always wanted to do this as a future profession but after some research I'm having my doubts.


-It requires 12 years of post-secondary education. I cried/freaked out when I read this. I'll be 30 by the time I'm done all this schooling. When will I get married!? 32?! AHH! Do I really want to spend almost half my life in school? I want to have a life. Have a job. Enjoy life.

Only 10 people in Canada are accepted into the program each year.

~~~~

WHY DOES THIS PROGRAM REQUIRE SO MUCH TRAINING!??!?!?! *freaking out*

~~~~

..I think in Taiwan its only..9 years? This is unfair. And also totally rocked the boat on whether I want to pursue post-secondary education in Taiwan or Canada. Obviously the one that involves less time.

June 8: Government/Constitution Test, NBA Finals June 9: Interwar/WWI Quiz June 10: Go to library June 11: Do eng project June 12: WWII quiz. Commencement decoration @ 11:30 June 13: Cold war quiz June 14: Awards assemblies blk C. Poetry test. No dance June 15: Geography test. Math mock final. Dance rehersal @ 4:20 June 16: Math written final. SS mock final. Eng project due. Shortened school day. Country fair June 17: Study at library. Kevin's birthday June 18: Dance recital @ 4:30 June 19: Canada Post 1945 quiz. English final June 20: Math MC final June 21: June 22: SS provincial June 23: Fraserwood sports day June 24: Tom leaves June 25: June 26: SAT results June 27: Awards night, duck pond trip June 28: June 29: Report cards, Mandarin provincial June 30: SUMMER! ___________________________________________________________________________ Mahli just doesn't give up on the tests, quizzes, and hw. I need a break. I need summer. ___________________________________________________________________________ I need to stop procrastinating..

I'm done my SAT!!! This means I'm free. At least until a week before finals. Then its back to cramming. ~~~~ Came home and crashed on the sofa. (because I didnt have the energy to walk upstairs to my bed) :D

Haven't posted in awhile, or even commented, but I'm still here. :D Been crazy busy doing work experience, watching the first and second season of House, studying my ass of for SAT exam next sat. Which I find rather ironic. BUT......read the meme on and it was so amusing that I HAD to do it. And because I've been obsessing over those gorgeous guys on tv lately. Totally fits my current ..mood thingy. List ten fictional characters you'd shag, and then tag five friends. 1. Robert Chase [tv.House] I fell for his Australian accent and gorgeous hair. Lol. 2. Mike [tv.Desperate.Housewives] 3. Michael Vaughn [tv.Alias] 4. McDreamy aka Derek Shepard [tv.Grey's.Anatomy] 5. Aragorn [movie.LotR] Remember that vote in gr 8, Aragorn or Frodo? Well, I switched sides 6. Jack Sparrow [movie.PotC] 7. Gregory House [tv.House] 8. Alex Karev [tv.Grey's.Anatomy] 9. Jake Gyllenhaal [movie.Brokeback.Mountain] ..and I dont remember the character's name 10. Zoro [manga.One.Piece] *dreamy sigh*

Well well, I think I got in trouble today out on work experience. Apparently we aren't supposed to play tag on the playground. Heh;; Didn't know that. Well the supervisor told the teacher. Blah...

Anyways, yep, this is what I do when I get out of school early to "work". I eat lunch with the kids, go out and have recess. Sometimes we have PE and I'm the pitcher for California Kickball. Or they do fractions and I make sure they do it correctly. Or I read them a book. Mark tests. Whatever.

Today we went to see the school play, "Joseph and the Amazing Technicolour Coat". Then went out for PE. By that time it was the end of the day. Sweet~ I did nothing all day. I'm wondering, since Joseph is from the bible, are they actually allowed to put on the play? After all, you aren't supposed to promote any sort of religion at school...

I'm getting too old to be playing tag.

Today was fun. My throat is raw now, after all the screaming we did.

Before I went, I bought my really expensive shoes T-T Lemme tell you something, having small feet really sucks. The smallest the stores carry is size 6, and usually they're out of those...so either I have to get a bigger size or buy kid's shoes. Sad, isn't it? After..2 hours, I finally found a pair I like AND fits me. Wow...

Yeah, Frank came with us (me and Tom) for some reason. Huh. AND he went to Sally's. He doesnt even know her that well..

Well, we played some Pictionary at SK's. That was a lot of fun. Lots of yelling and screaming XD Our team totally owned~~~~~~ Then charades. Somehow we gave up on scores and just made funny "skits" up instead. 

And Josh went!! Wow..I didn't know he was coming. Totally surprised me when I saw him on the bus on my way to the mall..

We made Jack make "girl" faces. They were soooooo un-manly!!! xppppppppp Haha, so Tom and Kevin tried to "aruba/happy corner" him. But they were GOOOD pictures. Put them up Jen!!!

And we watched the guys play Kingdom Hearts II. A lot of yelling went on. Haha, can't help that the characters are hot..except Mickey Mouse's troop. Haha~~ <3 Mickey.

Oh yeah, how can I forget our sword/noodle battles~~ Haha, we even had shields!! That was funnn...

...and I love how Kevin kept stuffing his face. Pig.

I'm thinking about quitting MSN. :O I spend waaay too much time on the computer, and MSN is partially the reason why. Maybe....maybe then I'll concentrate on my work. And to better in school :D Sounds good doesn't it? The studying, prolly not gunna happen tho.

I wanna go back to Taiwan for a visit. See my dad, grandparents, cousins, etc. I wanted to go back either over summer or winter vacay, but my mom said its too expensive to go back. Wtf, then why did we even immigrate here if we cant afford to go back? So we got into this not really argument seeing as how there wasn't as much yelling as there would usually have been. But there were tears. From me. I realized how much I miss my dad, even though I'm used to not having him around. Now....I don't know what to say anymore..

Ok, real quick update before I go to bed.

-Today is the first day since school started again that I'm done my hw before 11
-I'm sick. My eyes are swollen, nose plugged, throat sore, voice hoarse, body tired, brain dead...and whatever other ailment I've missed.
-Mock interview today. My interviewer was incredibly hard. He asked why they should hire ME. Still haven't figured that one out.
-Watched Macbeth in english class. I slept through the first 20 minutes. I'm horrible at recognizing characters. I can't tell the difference between Macbeth, Macduff, King _____, all the other guy characters. I think they look the same. Only way I can tell is by the crown the current king wears, and our teachers commentary.
-Learned quadratic formula in math. So easy. Hard to believe gr 12 math will be so much more challenging.
-My mom's back from Taiwan! That means I get a ride to school! Whee~~~ No more waking up at 7.
-I have just learned how good my dad is at chinese calligraphy. My mom brought some of his writing over. I hope she plans to frame it and put it up on the wall. Yes, its that good.

I can't spell sleep right. This is sad. Its Spring Break and I'm living on 10 hours of sleep over 2 days, while 3 days ago I slept 12 hours in a day. This totally sucks. Well my mom was going back to Taiwan so we stayed up chatting till pretty late. Then I didn't want her to leave in the morning without saying goodbye, so I slept light, waking up at the sound of her alarm clock in the next room. And then..I slept over at Donna's. No need to mention it, we slept late, as per the unwritten agreement about sleepovers. Got up at 6:15 :O Donna's dad woke us up, cause I needed to get home and get ready to go to CSI Academy at BCIT. Hehe.

Hmm, today was...informative, and someone appalling. We had presenters talking about forensic science in general, and the requirements, then the surrey coroner came to talk about her role and what coroners do, which is investigate the cause of sudden unforseen death. After lunch we watched a pathologist open up a dead person's body. *I forgot what the word for that is* On video. Thank god. But right after lunch...ugh. Violent descriptions follow, highlight to read (in case some ppl dont) It was shocking, the speed in which she first sliced through the skin on the head, peeled it back over on itself like a banana so that even tho the person was face up, we could no longer see his face, and then used a saw to cut through the skull. She then took out the brain, severing all the tissues and membranes holding it to the inside of the head. Then a Y-shape was drawn down the body. Imagine a blade slicing right through skin. It was like the frog dissection we did in biology once again. Only on a larger scale, on a human, and done waaaay faster. It was frightening, the precision with which she cut away the skin and peeled it open. I remember when we did the frong dissection there was the yellow fat. Once again, the human body was like that. Clumps of fat, and you could also see muscle. It was very interesting but stomach turning. She then made two vertical incisions and opened the person "like a book". Ugh, I remember shuddering at that, comparing doing an autopsy (thats the word!!!) on a human to opening a book. Then the person in charge turned off the video. It was really graphic, and she said the look on some people's faces weren't all that great. But it was definitely an experience I wouldn't have missed. Wow.
Then we had more presentations. With me starting to doze off in my chair, I think we talked about prevention of injury to rescuers so incidents like with the firemen in 9/11 dont happen again. And arson. About how evidence is left, especially bugs, even after a fire, and the dead person who has been burnt still makes it through the fire somewhat intact.

Random fact: Identical twins may have the same DNA but will not have the same fingerprints.

~~~~~~
When I phone, I expect someone to pick up. I want to talk. But theres no one there. In my current mood, that pisses me off. I feel a headache coming on...and excuse whatever mistakes I may have made typing this. You have no idea how many times I hit backspace.

~~~~~~
I feel sorry for my brother now. I yelled at him when I got home because he didnt eat the salad I prepared him, and didnt even bother putting any of the salad or turkey back into the fridge. I get scary when I'm tired.

I'm really really really frustrated right now. Maybe I haven't changed gears yet. I dont know hwat it is, but I'm doing as well as I hoped in my classes. I just may end up with a B in socials. I failed the essay part of our test. I'm serious. 8/20. I wasn't supposed to write in narrative. How am I supposed to know that!? And...I did the same thing for english. I just hope I get a better mark..Math isn't going as well as I hope either. I'm 5th in the class;; Oh yeah, and the koreans in my class are cheating during tests, comparing their answers, so someone has 100%. I'm really frustrated cause I actually work for my mark. I want to tell the teacher, but I dont know if its wise. Any suggestions?

At least spring break is coming. My salvation~

<font size=8>CSI ACADEMY, HERE I COME!!!!</font>

Whoopie!! I got accepted into the forensics program at BCIT. This means I get to spend spring break doing cool labs and stuff. :D:D I cant believe I got in. Just when I was starting to lose hope. HEHEHEHE *HYPER*

Now...back to concentrating on math. I just had a brain wave too...

Well, once again, its the weekend and I'm crazy busy with all my usual activities. As usual. However, there's one thing thats characterized this week, making it different from all the rest. I handed in my resignation letter in at Pizza Hut yesterday. Yep, thats right, I'm quitting my job.

My life has been hectic, always bustling from here to there and cramming in homework in those spare moments. Well no more. I've been gradually quitting lessons to allow myself more free time, and thus, less stress. :D Yay!~~ Although I'll be sad to see my salary go. It wasnt huge amounts, but it let me have more control over my spending and finances. However, I -do- realize that I'm still a student, and shouldn't be worrying over monetary matters.

It took awhile for me to finally realize that I don't need to be working and so, in a month, I shall be free! And there also goes my independance for money..

My mom is totally wrapped up in her volunteering junk for TzuChi that she's asking for my friends phone and phoning them up to ask them to go to this and that or to help this and that. Wtf...isn't it enough that you have to do this to me, can't you spare my friends? The latest victim was Kevin...I thought she was going to ask him about volunteering thing at the Senior's Home, but NOO, its to go to this TzuChi meeting.

Yeah. Volunteering is good. I get the point. But thats ALL you do these days. Pisses the hell out of me.

....yes, I know SK's already made a list, but there was 'make a to do list' on my mental to-do list... if that made any sense at all, i'd be happy. Anywho...

+study ch 1 math
+do 3 practice fermat contest practice wkst (btw, does anyone know if we can use calculator/scrap paper..that sorta stuff?)
+cover letter/resume
+keep up with portfolio. do as much as possible for 3.1
+do eng paragraph

You Know You're Chinese When....
You unwrap Christmas gifts very carefully, so you can save and reuse the wrapping (and especially those bows) next year. You only buy Christmas cards after Christmas, when they are 50% off. When there is a sale on toilet paper, you buy 100 rolls and store them in your closet or in the bedroom of an adult child who has moved out.Not 100, but more than usual You have a vinyl table cloth on your kitchen table. Your stove is covered with aluminum foil. You use the dishwasher as a dish rack. You keep a Thermos of hot water available at all times. You eat all meals in the kitchen.I'm supposed to, but I dont You save grocery bags, tin foil, and tin containers. You use grocery bags to hold garbage. You always leave your shoes at the door. You have a piano in your living room. You twirl your pen around your fingers. Even if you're totally full, if someone says they're going to throw away the leftovers on the table, you'll finish them. You don't own any real Tupperware -- only a cupboard full of used but carefully rinsed margarine tubs, takeout containers, and jam jars. Half half ah You also use the jam jars as drinking glasses.Ew You've eaten a red bean Popsicle. You bring oranges (or other produce) with you as a gift when you visit people's homes. You have a collection of miniature shampoo bottles that you take every time you stay in a hotel. The condiments in your fridge are either Price Club sized or come in plastic packets, which you save/steal every time you get take out or go to McDonald's. Ditto for paper napkins. You never order room service. You carry a stash of your own food whenever you travel (and travel means any car ride longer than 15 minutes). These travel snacks are always dried. As in not just dried plums, dried ginger, and beef/pork jerky, but dried cuttlefish (SQUID). Your parents vehemently refuse the sack of gold coin oranges that their guests just brought just to be courteous. Your dad thinks he can fix everything himself.O.o far from it You majored in something practical like engineering, medicine or law. When you go to a dance party, there are a wall of guys surrounding the dance floor trying to look cool. You live with your parents and you are 30 years old (and they prefer it that way). Or if you're married and 30 years old, you live in the apartment next door to your parents, or at least in the same neighborhood. You don't use measuring cups. You feel like you've gotten a good deal if you didn't pay tax. You beat eggs with chopsticks. Your parents' house is always cold. You have a teacup with a cover on it. You reuse teabags. Your mom drives her Mercedes to the Price Club. You tip Chinese delivery guys / waiters more. You're a wok user. You like Chinese films in their original undubbed versions. You have acquired a taste for bittermelon. You like congee with thousand year old eggs. You prefer your shrimp with the heads and legs still attached -- it means they're fresh. You never call your parents just to say hi. You always cook too much. If you don't live at home, when your parents call, they ask if you've eaten rice, even if it's midnight. Your parents tell you to boil herbs and stay inside when you get sick. They also tell you not to eat fried foods or baked goods because they produce hot air. Your parents never go to the movies. Your parents send money to their relatives in China. You use a face cloth. Your parents use a clothes line. You eat every last grain of rice in your bowl, but don't eat the last piece of food on the table. You starve yourself before going to all you can eat sushi. You've joined a CD club at least once. You know someone who can get you a good deal on jewelry or electronics. You never discuss your love life with your parents. Your parents are never happy with your grades. You keep most of your money in a savings account. You've been on the Love Boat or know someone who has. Your toothpaste tubes are all squeezed paper-thin. You love Chinese Martial Arts films. You have Tupperware in your fridge with three bites of rice or one leftover chicken wing. Shao Lin and Wu Tang actually mean something to you. You love to go to $1.75 movies. You love to go to $1.50 movies even more. You never order sweet-n-sour pork, egg foo young, or chop suey at a Chinese restaurant. You hate to spend more than $5 for lunch. Someone in your family drives a Honda... with custom rims. You have a Chinese knick-knack hanging from your rear-view mirror. You like to eat chicken feet. You suck on fish heads and fish fins. You turn bright red after drinking two tablespoons of beer. You can get a buzz on Coors O'Douls or Miller Sharps. You look like you are eighteen. You only buy used cars. You have more than five remotes in your house. You leave the plastic on the lampshade for ten years or more. You can't bear to throw things away. Your dad washes his hair four times a day, or never at all. Your unassisted vision is worse than 20/500. You've worn glasses at least since the fifth grade. Your parents (or some other close relative) own a grocery store or restaurant. You drive around looking for the cheapest gas. You add twice the amount of water recommended when making orange juice from concentrate. You've never seen your parents hug. Your grandmother lives with you and your family.Kinda..in Taiwan they do You never order desserts at restaurants. You always have water when dining out. You say "aiya!" and "wah!" frequently. You love Las Vegas, slot machines, and blackjack. You love to play mah jong. You have to read all your parents' mail written in English. You are constantly being set up with uninteresting (and usually ugly) people by your parents. You hate eating cheese. You have a big aquarium filled with colorful fish somewhere in your house. Your mother is strangely obsessed with plants. White people look at you strangely if you tell them you are Buddhist. You notice the main topic at family get-togethers is food. You seldom ever owned new clothes if you were a second child. Your folks never speak under 10 decibels at family gatherings. You never made the school football or basketball team.Ok, I plan to.. You have two middle initials instead of one. You grow your own bean sprouts in the kitchen. Your mother made you peel water chestnuts and snow peas. You have an lonely unmarried relative who frequently drops by during dinner time. You received little red envelopes containing money on special occasions. You use the underside of a porcelain bowl to sharpen your knives. You cut your own hair? or had someone in your family do it. Your grandmother has a lot of gold teeth? especially in front. You keep fresh garlic and ginger in the kitchen at all times. You know what the term "lemon" or a "banana" means. You only have to shave every other day (maybe). You wash and reuse ziplock bags. You know at least three people named Alan Wong. You never drank milk after eating cherries. Your parents collect jade jewelry. You always drink tea after a meal. Your dad owns at least one bird. Your parents grow vegetables in a garden. You use doilies to decorate your furniture. Your grandmother rapped your knuckles with her chopsticks while reaching food with your fingers. You're proud to be Chinese - and you pass these jokes on to all your Chinese friends!
